      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Due to floating point rounding the resulting array may not be Hermitian,\nthe diagonal elements may not be 1, and the elements may not satisfy the\ninequality abs(a) <= 1. The real and imaginary parts are clipped to the\ninterval [-1,  1] in an attempt to improve on that situation but is not\nmuch help in the complex case."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "This function accepts but discards arguments "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "bias"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ddof"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".  This is\nfor backwards compatibility with previous versions of this function.  These\narguments had no effect on the return values of the function and can be\nsafely ignored in this and previous versions of numpy."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In this example we generate two random arrays, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "xarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "yarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", and\ncompute the row-wise and column-wise Pearson correlation coefficients,\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "R"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". Since "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "rowvar"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is  true by  default, we first find the row-wise\nPearson correlation coefficients between the variables of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "xarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "rng = we.random.default_rng(seed=42)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xarr = rng.random((3, 3))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[0.77395605, 0.43887844, 0.85859792],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [0.69736803, 0.09417735, 0.97562235],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [0.7611397 , 0.78606431, 0.12811363]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "R1 = we.corrcoef(xarr)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "R1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[ 1.        ,  0.99256089, -0.68080986],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.99256089,  1.        , -0.76492172],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.68080986, -0.76492172,  1.        ]])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If we add another set of variables and observations "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "yarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", we can\ncompute the row-wise Pearson correlation coefficients between the\nvariables in "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "xarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "yarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "yarr = rng.random((3, 3))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "yarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[0.45038594, 0.37079802, 0.92676499],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [0.64386512, 0.82276161, 0.4434142 ],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [0.22723872, 0.55458479, 0.06381726]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "R2 = we.corrcoef(xarr, yarr)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "R2"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[ 1.        ,  0.99256089, -0.68080986,  0.75008178, -0.934284  ,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "        -0.99004057],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.99256089,  1.        , -0.76492172,  0.82502011, -0.97074098,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "        -0.99981569],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.68080986, -0.76492172,  1.        , -0.99507202,  0.89721355,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         0.77714685],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.75008178,  0.82502011, -0.99507202,  1.        , -0.93657855,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "        -0.83571711],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.934284  , -0.97074098,  0.89721355, -0.93657855,  1.        ,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         0.97517215],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.99004057, -0.99981569,  0.77714685, -0.83571711,  0.97517215,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         1.        ]])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Finally if we use the option "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "rowvar=False"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", the columns are now\nbeing treated as the variables and we will find the column-wise Pearson\ncorrelation coefficients between variables in "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "xarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "yarr"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "R3 = we.corrcoef(xarr, yarr, rowvar=False)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "R3"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[ 1.        ,  0.77598074, -0.47458546, -0.75078643, -0.9665554 ,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         0.22423734],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.77598074,  1.        , -0.92346708, -0.99923895, -0.58826587,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "        -0.44069024],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.47458546, -0.92346708,  1.        ,  0.93773029,  0.23297648,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         0.75137473],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.75078643, -0.99923895,  0.93773029,  1.        ,  0.55627469,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         0.47536961],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [-0.9665554 , -0.58826587,  0.23297648,  0.55627469,  1.        ,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "        -0.46666491],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.22423734, -0.44069024,  0.75137473,  0.47536961, -0.46666491,"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "         1.        ]])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
  "canonical_name": "corrcoef",
  "category": "counted_custom",
  "cost_formula": "n^2 * m",
  "cost_formula_latex": "$n^2 \\cdot m$",
