  "example": {
    "code": "import whest as we\n\nimport whest as we\n\nrng = we.random.default_rng(seed=42)\n\nxarr = rng.random((3, 3))\n\nxarr\n\nR1 = we.corrcoef(xarr)\n\nR1\n\nyarr = rng.random((3, 3))\n\nyarr\n\nR2 = we.corrcoef(xarr, yarr)\n\nR2\n\nR3 = we.corrcoef(xarr, yarr, rowvar=False)\n\nR3",
    "output": "array([[0.77395605, 0.43887844, 0.85859792],\n       [0.69736803, 0.09417735, 0.97562235],\n       [0.7611397 , 0.78606431, 0.12811363]])\n\narray([[ 1.        ,  0.99256089, -0.68080986],\n       [ 0.99256089,  1.        , -0.76492172],\n       [-0.68080986, -0.76492172,  1.        ]])\n\narray([[0.45038594, 0.37079802, 0.92676499],\n       [0.64386512, 0.82276161, 0.4434142 ],\n       [0.22723872, 0.55458479, 0.06381726]])\n\narray([[ 1.        ,  0.99256089, -0.68080986,  0.75008178, -0.934284  ,\n        -0.99004057],\n       [ 0.99256089,  1.        , -0.76492172,  0.82502011, -0.97074098,\n        -0.99981569],\n       [-0.68080986, -0.76492172,  1.        , -0.99507202,  0.89721355,\n         0.77714685],\n       [ 0.75008178,  0.82502011, -0.99507202,  1.        , -0.93657855,\n        -0.83571711],\n       [-0.934284  , -0.97074098,  0.89721355, -0.93657855,  1.        ,\n         0.97517215],\n       [-0.99004057, -0.99981569,  0.77714685, -0.83571711,  0.97517215,\n         1.        ]])\n\narray([[ 1.        ,  0.77598074, -0.47458546, -0.75078643, -0.9665554 ,\n         0.22423734],\n       [ 0.77598074,  1.        , -0.92346708, -0.99923895, -0.58826587,\n        -0.44069024],\n       [-0.47458546, -0.92346708,  1.        ,  0.93773029,  0.23297648,\n         0.75137473],\n       [-0.75078643, -0.99923895,  0.93773029,  1.        ,  0.55627469,\n         0.47536961],\n       [-0.9665554 , -0.58826587,  0.23297648,  0.55627469,  1.        ,\n        -0.46666491],\n       [ 0.22423734, -0.44069024,  0.75137473,  0.47536961, -0.46666491,\n         1.        ]])",
    "source": "derived"
  },
  "href": "/docs/api/ops/corrcoef",
  "name": "corrcoef",
  "next": {
    "href": "/docs/api/ops/correlate",
    "label": "we.correlate"
  },
  "notes": "Pearson correlation coefficients.",
  "notes_sections": [
    "Due to floating point rounding the resulting array may not be Hermitian, the diagonal elements may not be 1, and the elements may not satisfy the inequality abs(a) <= 1. The real and imaginary parts are clipped to the interval [-1,  1] in an attempt to improve on that situation but is not much help in the complex case.",
    "This function accepts but discards arguments `bias` and `ddof`.  This is for backwards compatibility with previous versions of this function.  These arguments had no effect on the return values of the function and can be safely ignored in this and previous versions of numpy."
  ],
  "numpy_ref": "np.corrcoef",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "body": [
        "A 1-D or 2-D array containing multiple variables and observations.",
        "Each row of `x` represents a variable, and each column a single",
        "observation of all those variables. Also see `rowvar` below."
      ],
      "name": "x",
      "type": "array_like"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "An additional set of variables and observations. `y` has the same",
        "shape as `x`."
      ],
      "name": "y",
      "type": "array_like, optional"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "If `rowvar` is True (default), then each row represents a",
